headlines.description: — Damian Lillard's fast start ensured that the Detroit Pistons couldn't get any ideas they might end their lengthy skid against the Milwaukee Bucks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks roll to 146-114 blowout as Pistons suffer their 23rd consecutive loss

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 42 points and grabbed 15 rebounds, and the Philadelphia 76ers handed the injury-depleted Charlotte Hornets their worst loss in franchise history, 135-82 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores 42 points as 76ers hand Hornets worst loss in franchise history, 135-82

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen had 25 points and 14 rebounds, Donovan Mitchell added 22 points and a career-high 13 assists, and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Atlanta Hawks 127-119 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jarrett Allen has 25 points and 14 rebounds, Cavaliers beat Hawks 127-119

headlines.description: — Kyle Lowry called the play. Kevin Love set the screen. Jimmy Butler took the shot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler wins it at the buzzer for Miami, as Heat top Bulls 118-116

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored a season-high 40 points and grabbed 12 rebounds, Anthony Edwards added 37 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves pulled away in the second half to dominate the short-handed Indiana Pacers 127-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns scores 40 and Edwards has 37 as Timberwolves top short-handed Pacers 127-109

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Brooklyn called timeout, unable to stop Stephen Curry, then the two-time MVP and injured teammate Gary Payton II looked right at each other and both released a celebratory roar.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry's big fourth quarter sends Warriors past Nets 124-120 to end three-game skid

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander hit a turnaround jumper with a second left, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied to beat the Denver Nuggets 118-117 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander makes winning jumper with a second left as Thunder edge Nuggets 118-117

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had a triple-double with 40 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists to help the Dallas Mavericks beat the Portland Trail Blazers 131-120 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic has triple-double in Mavericks' 131-120 victory over Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Keegan Murray made 12 3-pointers, two shy of the NBA record, and scored a career-high 47 points in the Sacramento Kings' 125-104 victory over the Utah Jazz on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keegan Murray makes 12 3-pointers, scores career-high 47 points to lead Kings past Jazz, 125-104

events.name: New York Knicks at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — A month ago, the Los Angeles Clippers were in a six-game skid. They've certainly got things figured out now.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers throttle Knicks 144-122 for their NBA-best 7th straight victory
